✅ COMPREHENSIVE TAKEAWAYS: POLICY INFERENCE WITH PYMDP INTEGRATION
================================================================================
🤖 PyMDP Planning Agent integration successful - Multi-step policy inference demonstrated!

🔍 POLICY INFERENCE FOUNDATIONS:
1. Policy inference minimizes Expected Free Energy (EFE) over action sequences
2. Multi-step EFE = Σ_t [Pragmatic_t + Epistemic_t] across time horizon
3. Pragmatic value captures preference satisfaction (-E[C_t])
4. Epistemic value captures expected information gain potential
5. PyMDP construct_policies() generates all possible policy sequences
6. Longer horizons enable better long-term EFE optimization

🚀 PYMDP AGENT INTEGRATION:
7. Agent class performs sophisticated multi-step policy inference
8. EFE-based planning guides goal-directed navigation and behavior
9. Agent.infer_policies() implements optimal policy selection
10. Multi-step planning handles complex environmental constraints
11. Policy inference integrates seamlessly with state inference
12. Sophisticated planning enables complex goal-directed behaviors

🔬 PyMDP Methods Demonstrated & Validated:
- pymdp.agent.Agent() with multi-step policy inference (policy_len=3)
